Senior DevOps Engineer Interview – Amazon

Round 1 – System Thinking (45 min)

• Walk me through how a user request flows through your system from DNS → Load Balancer → Service → Pod → Database.
• Your Kubernetes pods are restarting every few minutes. What’s your debugging flow?
• Your system latency suddenly increased after a deployment. What would you check first?
• Traffic increases 10x during peak hours. Which components become bottlenecks?
• Your monitoring didn’t detect an outage for 10 minutes. What went wrong?

⸻

Round 2 – Production Debugging (60 min)

• Your cluster nodes are healthy but users get 502 errors. Where do you investigate?
• Redis latency spikes during peak traffic. How do you trace the root cause?
• HPA didn’t scale even though CPU usage is high. Why could this happen?
• A deployment introduced a memory leak. Which signals expose it early?

⸻

Round 3 – Engineering Depth (30 min)

• How do you design systems that fail gracefully?
• How do you reduce MTTR in production systems?
• How do you prevent repeated incidents in a platform team?
